    "Let K be a finitely generated field over Q and e ≥ 2.",
    "Then, for almost all σ ∈ G e K, the following statement holds: for any finite extension L of K[σ] and any semiabelian variety A over L, the group A(L) is the direct sum of a finite torsion subgroup and a free Z-module of rank ℵ 0.",
